From d7363ea0c047807aecb0acf7f8076882ecfc6592 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:48:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.4b: Decompose ServiceRequests god-component into 6 focused
 components
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Second and final half of T2.4. Breaks the 532-line ServiceRequests.jsx
god-component into a thin orchestrator (130 lines) plus six focused
child components and a utilities module. Closes T2.4 entirely.

New file layout:

  src/pages/ServiceRequests.jsx (orchestrator, 130 lines)
    - holds top-level state: selected, showMobileDetail, showNew
    - two useQuery calls: ServiceRequest list + role-scoped User list
    - role-scoped client filter (admin sees all; TC/investor see only
      their own requests — Base44 single-key filter can't express the
      OR so we fetch and filter)
    - composes the 3 top-level children below

  src/components/service-requests/RequestList.jsx (88 lines)
    - sidebar with request list + status badges
    - pure presentation, all data from props

  src/components/service-requests/RequestDetail.jsx (160 lines)
    - detail pane: header, stepper, timestamps, notes
    - owns advanceStatus mutation (scalar writes only — no race)
    - composes DocumentsSection + CommentsSection

  src/components/service-requests/DocumentsSection.jsx (125 lines)
    - documents list + upload button
    - owns uploading state + file size/MIME validation
    - PRESERVES T2.5 refetch-before-write for race safety

  src/components/service-requests/CommentsSection.jsx (119 lines)
    - comments thread + composer
    - owns draft comment state
    - PRESERVES T2.5 refetch-before-write for race safety

  src/components/service-requests/ProgressStepper.jsx (51 lines)
    - horizontal stage indicator (Requested -> Accepted ->
      In Progress -> Completed), extracted verbatim

  src/components/service-requests/NewRequestModal.jsx (168 lines)
    - party picker + deal title + notes + create mutation
    - invalidates ServiceRequest cache on create

  src/lib/serviceRequestUtils.js (52 lines)
    - pure helpers: STAGES, STATUS_NEXT, STATUS_COLORS,
      MAX_FILE_SIZE, ALLOWED_FILE_TYPES, formatRequestDate,
      canAdvanceStatus

Behavior preserved exactly:
- Role-scoped request filter (TC/investor see only their own, admin
  sees all)
- Role-scoped counterparty picker (TC sees investors, investor sees
  TCs, admin sees all approved members)
- Admins cannot create new requests (button hidden)
- advanceStatus only available to TC and admin
- Mobile nav: hide list when detail is open, back button returns
- Progress stepper with animated spinner on current stage
- Timestamps grid showing all 4 stages
- Notes section (conditional on request.notes)
- Document upload: 25MB cap, MIME whitelist, chip display
- Comment thread with right-aligned 'mine' styling
- Enter to post comment (Shift+Enter for newline)

Behavior improvements:
- Selected request syncs via onRequestUpdated callback from mutation
  handlers instead of waiting for list refetch — detail pane updates
  immediately after advance/comment/upload
- ARIA labels added to icon-only buttons (back, close, upload, send,
  new-request)
- advanceStatus error now toasts instead of failing silently (was
  already a catch block but the user never saw feedback if it was
  a pre-existing server error state)

T2.5 race fix preservation:
DocumentsSection and CommentsSection both preserve the refetch-before-
write pattern from T2.5. Each includes an explicit comment pointing at
T2.5 so the fix survives future edits. advanceStatus does NOT need
this pattern — it writes scalar fields only (status + one timestamp),
no array read-modify-write.

Mutation strategy (same as T2.4a and all prior T2.2 slices):
No useMutation conversion — each mutation handler has its own shape
(advanceStatus toasts on error, uploadDocument validates file first,
addComment refetches-before-write). useMutation's generic wrappers
add indirection without simplifying the logic. queryClient.invalidate
after success is enough.

Files:
  Changed: src/pages/ServiceRequests.jsx (532 -> 130 lines)
  Added:   src/components/service-requests/{7 new files}
  Added:   src/lib/serviceRequestUtils.js

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 0 warnings on all new files
- npm run build: succeeds
